title: Younger, more diverse Alberta electorate could be a boon for opposition parties
text: The CBC's Susan Bonner finds a desire for change in once rock-solid Conservative Alberta. Some eight seats are in play in Calgary and Edmonton, and a breakthrough for the opposition parties could make the difference in forming a government. ...
